            UIC Business Marketing Research Class Collaborates with Nonprofit Revolution Institute on Survey Project
          Heading link



 
Copy link



Last summer, Serkan Saka’s Marketing Research (MKTG 462) class collaborated with Camille Levi, director of Business Development at the Revolution Institute (RI), on a project that yielded tremendous results for the nonprofit organization. Primarily serving the African American and Latinx communities of Chicago’s south and west sides, RI’s mission is to address the wealth gap in the workforce development and social enterprise space.


